      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="506-14W2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">WHO HAD BEEN MUCH ABUSED IN MANY INVETERATE LIBELS.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-1"> T<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">HE</hi> greatest monarch may be stabb'd by night,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-2"> And fortune help the murderer in his flight;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-3"> The vilest ruffian may commit a rape,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-4"> Yet safe from injured innocence escape;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-5"> And calumny, by working under ground,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-6"> Can, unrevenged, the greatest merit wound.What's to be done? Shall wit and learning choose</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-7"> To live obscure, and have no fame to lose?</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-8"> By Censure frighted out of Honour's road,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-9"> Nor dare to use the gifts by Heaven bestow'd?</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-10"> Or fearless enter in through Virtue's gate,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-506-14W2-line-11"> And buy distinction at the dearest rate.506-14W2   </l></lg></div>
